  "market_context": "Daily chart showed a sweep of prior swing low forming high resistance liquidity; bias turned bullish after price closed back inside the wick range. Hourly confirmed bullish CISD, leading to 5-minute propulsion block entry targeting NWOG and previous day high.",
  "key_observation": "The daily swing low was swept but price closed back inside the range, creating high resistance liquidity at the low—this became a support zone for bullish continuation once hourly CISD confirmed.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: On the daily chart (CL1!), identified a swept swing low with long lower wick (to ~62.00) and close near 63.50, forming high resistance liquidity; bias set bullish as price closed back inside the wick range.",
    "Step 2: Dropped to hourly chart to confirm structure: observed closure through the series of down-close candles that formed the low, confirming a change in state of delivery (CISD) and validating the bullish bias.",
    "Step 3: Identified a sweep of the prior low as a point of interest on the hourly, then dropped to 5-minute chart to locate entry setup.",
    "Step 4: On the 5-minute chart, waited for closure above the down-close candles forming the low, which created a propulsion block; entered long at market with stop below the new protected low.",
    "Step 5: Targeted expansion to the new week opening gap (NWOG) and previous day high, achieving 2R+ move."
  ],
  "outcome": "Successful long trade reaching NWOG and previous day high, achieving >2R reward.",
  "lessons": "A swept daily swing low can become high-resistance liquidity that acts as support when price closes back inside the range; only trade continuation after CISD confirmation on intermediate timeframe and propulsion block formation on LTF.",
